===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun}}

# A family of [[language]]s spoken primarily in [[Iran]], [[Afghanistan]], [[Uzbekistan]], and [[Tajikistan]].

====Usage notes====
* Persian is the name applied to the official language of [[Iran]]. This language is also spoken in [[Tajikistan]] and some parts of [[Afghanistan]] and [[Uzbekistan]].
* The name "[[Farsi]]" (the local name for Persian) has recently developed currency in English to refer to the dialect spoken in Iran. Afghans usually call it [[Dari]], and the version spoken in Tajikistan is called Tajiki Persian or simply Tajiki.

